<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 26 at 3:38PM EDT  by NWS Raleigh</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of Montgomery and
southwestern Randolph Counties through 445 PM EDT...
At 337 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Troy, moving east at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Troy, North Carolina Zoo, Biscoe, Seagrove, Mount Gilead, Star,
Candor, Steeds, Eldorado and Pekin.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>Seek shelter NOW inside a sturdy building.</instruction>
